author: cjodea
msg: workaround for Axis Interop test failure on OS X
It's not really an OSX failure -- more of a slow Java/machine failure.  There appears to be
some timing related issue between Axis and Jetty whereby an Axis client is having problems
when a two-way invocation is directly followed by a one-way.  The Axis client intermittently
fails to correctly read the response from the server served up by Jetty.
